### Returning Template Output - Axum Handler - Rust

Source: https://github.com/askama-rs/askama/blob/master/book/src/frameworks.md

This Rust code snippet illustrates how to return the output of a rendered Askama template from an Axum handler function. It demonstrates wrapping the `String` result of `template.render()` within `axum::response::Html` to ensure it's sent with the correct `Content-Type`. The handler returns a `Result` with a custom `AppError` type.

```Rust
use axum::response::{Html, IntoResponse};

async fn handler() -> Result<impl IntoResponse, AppError> {
    …
    Ok(Html(template.render()?))
}
```

--------------------------------

### Implementing Custom Error Response - Axum - Rust

Source: https://github.com/askama-rs/askama/blob/master/book/src/frameworks.md

This Rust boilerplate demonstrates creating a custom `AppError` type compatible with Axum, designed for handling Askama rendering errors. It includes deriving `Debug`, `Display`, and `Error`, and implementing the `axum::response::IntoResponse` trait. This implementation converts the error into an HTTP response, setting the status code and rendering a dedicated error template (`error.html`) or a default message as the body.

```Rust
use axum::response::IntoResponse;
use askama::Template;

#[derive(Debug, displaydoc::Display, thiserror::Error)]
enum AppError {
    /// could not render template
    Render(#[from] askama::Error),
}

impl IntoResponse for AppError {
    fn into_response(self) -> Response {
        #[derive(Debug, Template)]
        #[template(path = "error.html")]
        struct Tmpl { … }

        let status = match &self {
            AppError::Render(_) => StatusCode::INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR,
        };
        let tmpl = Tmpl { … };
        if let Ok(body) = tmpl.render() {
            (status, Html(body)).into_response()
        } else {
            (status, "Something went wrong").into_response()
        }
    }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Returning Template Output - Actix-Web Handler - Rust

Source: https://github.com/askama-rs/askama/blob/master/book/src/frameworks.md

This Rust code snippet demonstrates how to integrate a rendered Askama template's output into an Actix-Web handler. It shows wrapping the `String` result of `template.render()` in `actix_web::web::Html` to return it as an HTML response. The handler signature uses a custom `AppError` type for error handling.

```Rust
use actix_web::web::Html;
use actix_web::{Responder, handler};

#[handler]
fn handler() -> Result<impl Responder, AppError> {
    …
    Ok(Html::new(template.render()?))
}
```

--------------------------------

### Returning Template Output - Poem Handler - Rust

Source: https://github.com/askama-rs/askama/blob/master/book/src/frameworks.md

This Rust snippet shows how to return the `String` output from `template.render()` as an HTML response within a Poem web framework handler. The `poem::web::Html` wrapper is used to ensure the content type is correctly set to HTML. The handler returns a `Result` using a custom `AppError` type for failures.

```Rust
use poem::web::Html;
use poem::{IntoResponse, handler};

#[handler]
async fn handler() -> Result<impl IntoResponse, AppError> {
    …
    Ok(Html(template.render()?))
}
```

--------------------------------

### Implementing Custom Error Response - Poem - Rust

Source: https://github.com/askama-rs/askama/blob/master/book/src/frameworks.md

This Rust code provides boilerplate for implementing a custom error type `AppError` that integrates with Poem's error handling. It uses `thiserror` and `displaydoc` for deriving standard error traits. It implements `poem::error::ResponseError` to provide an HTTP status code and `poem::IntoResponse` to convert the error into a Poem response, typically by rendering an error template (`error.html`). Requires `askama`, `thiserror`, and `displaydoc`.

```Rust
use poem::error::ResponseError;
use poem::http::StatusCode;
use poem::web::Html;
use poem::{IntoResponse, Response};
use askama::Template;

#[derive(Debug, displaydoc::Display, thiserror::Error)]
enum AppError {
    /// could not render template
    Render(#[from] askama::Error),
}

impl ResponseError for AppError {
    fn status(&self) -> StatusCode {
        match &self {
            AppError::Render(_) => StatusCode::INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR,
        }
    }
}

impl IntoResponse for AppError {
    fn into_response(self) -> Response {
        #[derive(Debug, Template)]
        #[template(path = "error.html")]
        struct Tmpl { … }

        let tmpl = Tmpl { … };
        if let Ok(body) = tmpl.render() {
            (self.status(), Html(body)).into_response()
        } else {
            (self.status(), "Something went wrong").into_response()
        }
    }
}
```

