    "content": "Task #4 status update: The base template and static file serving infrastructure was largely completed by Luca in commit `40f2d92`. I reviewed it from a CSS/frontend perspective and made two improvements:\n\n1. **`templates/base.html`**: Added `aria-atomic=\"true\"` to the aria-live region. This ensures screen readers announce the entire region content as a unit when updated, rather than just the changed text.\n\n2. **`static/css/main.css`**: Added HTMX indicator CSS to the components layer. The `.htmx-indicator` class (hidden by default, revealed when `.htmx-request` is active) provides loading state feedback during HTMX requests. This uses the motion-safe transition tokens so reduced-motion users see instant show/hide instead of a fade.\n\nThe skip-link class, landmark regions, CSS link, and all test assertions are already in place and passing. All 3 tests pass, fmt and clippy are clean.\n\nI also see uncommitted domain work (`email.rs`, `password.rs`, `user.rs`) and CI changes from other team members -- I'll only commit my CSS and template changes.\n\nReady to commit when you give the go-ahead, or I can proceed to help with Task #5 (registration) CSS components."
  }
}
